laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is markedly inflamed, demonstrating wall thickening and hyperemia, with extensive neighboring fat stranding, fascial thickening, and an abutting soft tissue density compatible with phlegmon. Focal perforation is seen at the mid aspect of the inflamed appendix, with a small amount of neighboring free fluid. No drainable fluid collections are seen.
Valuestr: 8.6 mg/dL, within normal range (8.4 - 10.3 mg/dL).
